A clean way to do this in Telerik ASP.NET Core Grid is:

Keep the toolbar simple
Add a small Help link/button beside the existing button
Use a reusable Kendo Window (recommended over Notification for help content)
Load different HTML help files dynamically
Store help HTML files in a dedicated folder
Use one reusable popup for all pages

This is the approach most teams use now because it scales nicely across many grids/pages.

✔ Recommended Architecture (Best Practice)

Use:

✅ Kendo Window for help popups
✅ External HTML help files
✅ One reusable popup component
✅ One JS function for all pages
✅ Lightweight CSS styling

Avoid:

Embedding giant HTML strings in Razor
Creating multiple notifications/windows per page
Inline styles everywhere
✔ Suggested Folder Structure

Inside your ASP.NET Core project:

wwwroot
 └── help
      ├── rebuilt-parts.html
      ├── estimates.html
      ├── archive.html
      ├── labour.html
      └── shared-grid-help.html

wwwroot
 └── css
      └── help-popup.css

wwwroot
 └── js
      └── help-popup.js

This keeps everything organized and source-control friendly.

✔ Step 1 — Add Toolbar Help Link

Update your toolbar template:

.ToolBar(tb => tb.ClientTemplate(
    "<button class='k-button k-button-icontext' onclick='window.openEstimatePopup(0)'>" +
    "<span class='k-icon k-i-plus'></span>Add New Rebuilt Parts Estimate</button>" +

    "<a class='k-button k-button-icontext k-grid-help-btn' " +
    "onclick=\"showHelpPopup('/help/rebuilt-parts.html')\">" +
    "<span class='k-icon k-i-question'></span>Help</a>"
))
✔ Step 2 — Add Reusable Kendo Window

Place this BELOW the grid.

<div id="helpWindow"></div>
✔ Step 3 — Initialize Kendo Window

Add this once on the page:

<script>
    $(document).ready(function () {

        $("#helpWindow").kendoWindow({
            width: "700px",
            height: "500px",
            title: "Online Help",
            visible: false,
            modal: true,
            actions: ["Close"],
            resizable: true
        });

    });

    function showHelpPopup(url) {

        var helpWindow = $("#helpWindow").data("kendoWindow");

        helpWindow.refresh({
            url: url
        });

        helpWindow.center().open();
    }
</script>
